</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25DEA0E5613FFA035EAD8B3175EFB7B" box="[747,827,1208,1230]" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(124, 125) Holotype, NMW.Z.2001.061.00039: (124) external left valve (Montage 
<superScript id="7C6F262F5613FFA0345BD8C5171DFB69" attach="left" box="[858,888,1230,1244]" fontSize="6" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">TM</superScript>
); (125) external right valve (SEM). (126–128) Paratype, NMW.Z.2001.061.00040 (SEM): (126) external; (127) prodissoconch; (128) hinge view. (129) 
<taxonomicName id="4C1AF0E45613FFA0341AD9031039FAAB" authority=", NMW. Z." authorityName="NMW. Z." box="[795,1116,1288,1310]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Cardita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis id="B96E57755613FFA0341AD90317B9FAA8" box="[795,988,1288,1309]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Cardita variegata</emphasis>
, NMW.Z.
</taxonomicName>
2000.086.00033, external right valve.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA58B675613FFA037C6D96B1669FA22" blockId="39.[159,1116,1376,1732]" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">
<emphasis id="B96E57755613FFA037C6D96B15D6FACD" box="[199,435,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Derivation of name.</emphasis>
Latin 
<emphasis id="B96E57755613FFA0350DD96B163AFACD" box="[524,607,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">pileolus</emphasis>
diminutive of 
<emphasis id="B96E57755613FFA0341CD96B1739FACD" box="[797,860,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">pileus</emphasis>
‘a cap’, referring to the form of the prodissoconch.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA58B675613FFAF37C6D9AB1640FA11" blockId="39.[159,1116,1376,1732]" lastBlockId="40.[154,1111,1254,1444]" lastPageId="40" lastPageNumber="3214" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">
<emphasis id="B96E57755613FFA037C6D9AB153AFA0D" box="[199,351,1440,1464]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Comparisons.</emphasis>
The only other carditid found on 
<collectingRegion id="49DE45855613FFA03427D99417FEFA02" box="[806,923,1439,1463]" country="Mauritius" name="Rodrigues" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Rodrigues</collectingRegion>
is referable to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1AF0E45613FFA0379ED9CB1627FA62" authority="(Bruguiere, 1792)" baseAuthorityName="Bruguiere" baseAuthorityYear="1792" box="[159,578,1471,1496]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Cardita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis id="B96E57755613FFA0379ED9CB150FFA6D" box="[159,362,1472,1496]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Cardita variegata</emphasis>
(Bruguière, 1792)
</taxonomicName>
and in its juvenile stage has a less angular outline (
<figureCitation id="132197E25613FFA03600D9EA1518FA4C" box="[257,381,1505,1529]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="39.[159,175,1208,1230]" captionTargetBox="[161,1111,175,1170]" captionTargetId="figure-131@39.[159,1116,170,1170]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGS. 124–129. (124–128) Centrocardita pileolata n. sp. (124, 125) Holotype, NMW.Z.2001.061.00039: (124) external left valve (MontageTM); (125) external right valve (SEM). (126–128) Paratype, NMW.Z.2001.061.00040 (SEM): (126) external; (127) prodissoconch; (128) hinge view. (129) Cardita variegata, NMW.Z. 2000.086.00033, external right valve." pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">figures 129</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132197E25613FFA0368CD9EA15DDFA4C" box="[397,440,1505,1529]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="40.[154,170,1094,1116]" captionTargetBox="[157,1111,173,1054]" captionTargetId="figure-102@40.[154,1111,170,1056]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGS. 130–134. (130, 131) Centrocardita pileolata n. sp., holotype, NMW.Z.2001.061.00039 (SEM): (130) internal right valve showing brood area; (131) close-up of embryo. (132, 133) Cardita variegata, NMW.Z.2000.086.0003 (SEM): (132) internal right valve; (133) hinge view. (134) Centrocardita pileolata, holotype, hinge view (SEM)." pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">132</figureCitation>
), a simple prodissoconch and a hinge with poorly developed lateral teeth (
<figureCitation id="132197E25613FFA03685DA081592F9AE" box="[388,503,1539,1563]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="40.[154,170,1094,1116]" captionTargetBox="[157,1111,173,1054]" captionTargetId="figure-102@40.[154,1111,170,1056]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGS. 130–134. (130, 131) Centrocardita pileolata n. sp., holotype, NMW.Z.2001.061.00039 (SEM): (130) internal right valve showing brood area; (131) close-up of embryo. (132, 133) Cardita variegata, NMW.Z.2000.086.0003 (SEM): (132) internal right valve; (133) hinge view. (134) Centrocardita pileolata, holotype, hinge view (SEM)." pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">figure 133</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8BF6965613FFA03511DA0816D5F9AE" author="Viader" box="[528,688,1539,1563]" firstAuthor="Viader" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213" pagination="127 - 155" refId="ref20923" refString="VIADER, R., 1951, New or unrecorded shells from Mauritius and its dependencies, Mauritius Institute Bulletin, 3 (2), 127 - 155." type="journal article" year="1951">Viader (1951)</bibRefCitation>
described two small carditids from 
<collectingCountry id="F30DCBF75613FFA0379EDA2E1576F988" box="[159,275,1573,1597]" name="Mauritius" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1AF0E45613FFA03622DA2E1580F988" authorityName="Viader" authorityYear="1951" box="[291,485,1573,1597]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Cardita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vaughani">
<emphasis id="B96E57755613FFA03622DA2E1580F988" box="[291,485,1573,1597]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Cardita vaughani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is equilateral with the maximum height axis running through the umbo, not behind the umbo as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1AF0E45613FFA035EFDA4C1713F9EA" authorityName="P. G. Oliver &amp; Holmes" authorityYear="2004" box="[750,886,1607,1631]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Centrocardita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pileolata">
<emphasis id="B96E57755613FFA035EFDA4C1713F9EA" box="[750,886,1607,1631]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">C. pileolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1AF0E45613FFA0348DDA4C1059F9EA" authorityName="Viader" authorityYear="1951" box="[908,1084,1607,1631]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Cardita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vinsoni">
<emphasis id="B96E57755613FFA0348DDA4C1059F9EA" box="[908,1084,1607,1631]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Cardita vinsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is inequilateral but the ribs are nodulose rather than scaly, the prodissoconch is not capped, and the carmine and brown coloration is not present in the 
<collectingRegion id="49DE45855613FFA03311DA8014B4F971" country="Mauritius" name="Rodrigues" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Rodrigues</collectingRegion>
shells. Many small carditids have been described from southern Africa and southern 
<collectingCountry id="F30DCBF7561CFFAF360AD8ED1510FB4B" box="[267,373,1254,1278]" name="Australia" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214">Australia</collectingCountry>
and we have reviewed the relevant literature (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8BF696561CFFAF34AFD8ED1037FB4B" author="Bartsch" box="[942,1106,1254,1278]" firstAuthor="Bartsch" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" pagination="1 - 305" refId="ref19469" refString="BARTSCH, P., 1915, Report on the Turton collection of South African marine mollusks, with additional notes on other South African shells contained in the United States National Museum, Smithsonian Institution United States National Museum Bulletin, 91, 1 - 305." type="journal article" year="1915">Bartsch, 1915</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8BF696561CFFAF379BD90C155DFAAA" author="Turton" box="[154,312,1287,1311]" firstAuthor="Turton" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" refId="ref20839" refString="TURTON, W. H., 1932, The Marine Shells of Port Alfred, S. Africa (London: Oxford University Press)." type="book" year="1932">Turton, 1932</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8BF696561CFFAF364AD90C1593FAAA" author="Barnard" box="[331,502,1287,1311]" firstAuthor="Barnard" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" pagination="361 - 593" refId="ref19430" refString="BARNARD, K. H., 1964, Contributions to the knowledge of South African marine mollusca. Part V Lamellibranchiata, Annals of the South African Museum, 47 (3), 361 - 593." type="journal article" year="1964">Barnard, 1964</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8BF696561CFFAF3508D90C172FFAAA" author="Lamprell and Healy" box="[521,842,1287,1311]" firstAuthor="Lamprell" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" refId="ref20058" refString="LAMPRELL, K. and HEALY, J., 1998, Bivalves of Australia, Vol. 2 (Leiden: Backhuys Publishers), 288 pp." type="book" year="1998">Lamprell and Healy, 1998</bibRefCitation>
). Most of the smaller taxa are referred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1AF0E4561CFFAF36A8D923167DFAF5" authorityName="E. A. Smith" authorityYear="1881" box="[425,536,1320,1344]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Carditella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96E5775561CFFAF36A8D923167DFAF5" box="[425,536,1320,1344]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214">Carditella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but some to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1AF0E4561CFFAF35DBD9231711FAF5" authorityName="Sacco" authorityYear="1899" box="[730,884,1320,1344]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Centrocardita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96E5775561CFFAF35DBD9231711FAF5" box="[730,884,1320,1344]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214">Centrocardita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(s. g. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1AF0E4561CFFAF34DAD9231028FAF5" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1925" box="[987,1101,1320,1344]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Vimentum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96E5775561CFFAF34DAD9231028FAF5" box="[987,1101,1320,1344]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214">Vimentum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and most are equilateral. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1AF0E4561CFFAF36D8D9411701FAD4" authority="(Smith, 1904)" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[473,868,1353,1378]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Carditella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="laticosta">
<emphasis id="B96E5775561CFFAF36D8D94116D0FAD7" box="[473,693,1354,1378]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214">Carditella laticosta</emphasis>
(Smith, 1904)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="F30DCBF7561CFFAF3478D9421073FAD4" box="[889,1046,1353,1377]" name="South Africa" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214">South Africa</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1AF0E4561CFFAF379BD9601600FA36" authority="(Smith, 1885)" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[154,613,1387,1411]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Carditella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="exulata" subGenus="Vimentum">
<emphasis id="B96E5775561CFFAF379BD96015D6FA36" box="[154,435,1387,1411]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214">C. (Vimentum) exulata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8BF696561CFFAF36CAD9601638FA36" author="Smith" box="[459,605,1387,1411]" firstAuthor="Smith" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" pagination="1 - 341" refId="ref20726" refString="SMITH, E. A., 1885, Report on the Lamellibronchiata. Reports of the Scientific Results of the voyage of HMS Challenger during the years of 1873 - 76, Zoology, 13, 1 - 341, 25 pls." type="book chapter" year="1885">Smith, 1885</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(South Australia) have oblique outlines but have poorly ornamented ribs.
</paragraph>
